data.text: As musical genres go, Christmas albums have got to be one of the most diverse. At one end of the spectrum there are the Ray Conniff Singers belting out spunky and earnest versions of "Frosty the Snowman" and "White Christmas" on their 1959 classic, "Christmas with Conniff."
